  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.1.0 (22323e2 2022-03-23T00:09:43.397848305+00:00)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge test\n\n### Operating System\n\nLinux\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nThis contract\r\n```solidity\r\n// SPDX-License-Identifier: UNLICENSED\r\npragma solidity 0.8.13;\r\n\r\ncontract HelloWorld {\r\n\r\n    event Message(string message);\r\n\r\n    string public message = \"Hello world\";\r\n    string[] public messages = [message];\r\n\r\n    function hello() public returns (string memory) {\r\n        emit Message(message);\r\n        return message;\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    function updateMessage(string calldata _message) public {\r\n        message = _message;\r\n        messages.push(_message);\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\nwith this test\r\n```solidity\r\n...\r\nfunction testUpdateMessage(string memory _message) public {\r\n        //cheats.assume(keccak256(abi.encodePacked(_message)) != keccak256(abi.encodePacked(\"\")));\r\n        hw.updateMessage(_message);\r\n        cheats.expectEmit(false, false, false, true);\r\n        emit Message(_message);\r\n        string memory message = hw.hello();\r\n        assertEq(_message, message);\r\n        \r\n        assertEq(_message, hw.messages(1));\r\n    }\r\n...\r\n```\r\nfails when `_message` is `\"\"`.\r\n\r\nTrace:\r\n```bash\r\n  [357484] HelloWorldTest::setUp()\r\n    ├─ → new HelloWorld@0xce71…c246\r\n    │   └─ ← 1280 bytes of code\r\n    └─ ← ()\r\n  [12158] HelloWorldTest::testUpdateMessage(\"\")\r\n    ├─ [4784] HelloWorld::updateMessage(\"\")\r\n    │   └─ ← ()\r\n    ├─ [0] VM::expectEmit(false, false, false, true)\r\n    │   └─ ← ()\r\n    ├─ emit Message(message: \"\")\r\n    ├─ [2850] HelloWorld::hello()\r\n    │   ├─ emit Message(message: \"\")\r\n    │   └─ ← \"\"\r\n    └─ ← \"Log != expected log\"\r\n```",
